items.headline: Welcome to the Order of the Stick Wiki
items.desc: The Order of the Stick (OOTS) is a webcomic written and illustrated by Rich Burlew, which pokes fun at tabletop roleplaying games and medieval fantasy.   In a world that loosely follows the rules of the role-playing game Dungeons and Dragons (D&D),  a group of six adventurers strive to save the world from an evil lich sorcerer.    The wiki serves as a collaborative database of information on the comic.

Die Serie ist die erste einer ganzen Reihe von Krimiserien, die von Dick Wolf produziert werden und das amerikanische Fernsehen seit nunmehr 20 Jahren prägen.

items.headline: This Wiki needs your help!
items.desc:
The Borderlands Fanon wiki is a very un-edited wiki, but with the help of many others, I hope to change that. It was originally founded by Ahalosniper who has since moved onto other wikia projects.

BFW is a place where people who love the Borderlands games can write their own fanfictions or participate in roleplays with other Borderlands fans. Well, it soon will be at least.

Please, anyone willing to help out this almost dead wiki, can you join soon.

Thanks,
BlazingLeopard, the newly appointed BFW admin.

items.name: Borderlands Wiki
items.title: Borderlands Wiki
items.headline: ¡Bienvenidos a Borderlands Wiki!
items.desc:
Envía un máximo de cuatro jugadores en cooperativo al fronterizo Pandora para buscar la legendaria Cámara alienígena. Este RPS, con su original sistema de juego, te permitirá personalizar a tu personaje mientras exploras y te enfrentas a tus enemigos en un frenético juego.

¿Y que seria un RPS sin botín? El innovador sistema de generación de contenido de Bordelands crea una variedad casi interminable de armas y objetos para personalizar a tu personaje. Los jugadores se pueden unir a las partidas de otros en cualquier momento o afrontar solos los desafíos de Borderlands. Todas estas características se combinan con un argumento rico y profundo y un estilo grafico audaz para crear una novedosa experiencia que desafía los convencionalismos de los FPS y RPG modernos

Ofrece un sistema cooperativo de 4 jugadores, combate en vehículos, muchas misiones y 2 tipos de recorridos. Todo esto para abatir el aburrimiento.

items.desc:
Order & Chaos: Online is a subscription based, fantasy, open-world, MMORPG that runs on iPhones, iPods and iPads, and android platforms!

Order & Chaos: Online features the typical fantasy MMORPG or Hack&Slash CRPG gameplay. The player controls one character in third person view, travels from quest hub to quest hub, and uses spells, talents and weapons to deal with unpleasantries on the way.

We give you everything you need to enter into battle, including information on maps, lore, items, pets, races, crafting, and PVP.

items.name: The Order: 1886 Wiki
items.title: The Order: 1886 Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to The Order - 1886 Wiki!
items.desc:
This wiki is about an upcoming game called The Order - 1886. 
The game is set to take place in an alternate universe in which the Industrial Revolution came about as an effort to win a centuries-old war against these inhuman enemies, among them the Lycans - a genetically distinct strain of bestial humans whom the populace have given the name of mythical beasts based on their appearance and shapeshifting powers. The game is rumored to include real-life historical figures, such as Nikol Tesla. It is scheduled to release in January of 2015 on the PS4. Come help us get the wiki ready for launch!

items.name: 1945-1991: Cold War world Wiki
items.title: 1945-1991: Cold War world Wiki
items.desc: Were you ever turned on by the Cuban Missile Crisis, Checkpoint Charlie, Exercise Reforger, Sputnik or the Berlin Wall? Here is a wiki devoted to the Cold War era! Our mission is to provide a state of the art, up-to-date wiki on all that deals with the Cold War that anyone can edit if they want to! You can swot up on your Cold War conflict between the USA and it's mostly democratic allies against the USSR and it's dictatorial left wing allies. The Second World War (1939-1945) was a monumental armed event in human history. In addition to being the most destructive war in human history, it set the stage for the post World War 2 world we have today. Just a few years after being allies, the 2 superpowers who had teamed up along side the UK, France, Poland and China to defeat Nazi Germany and it's cohorts became bitter geo-political rivals in a contest to see who would dominate the post World War 2 order that would last 45 years, ending with the demise of the Soviet Union. So, turn on your AN/PRC-77 Portable Transceiver  (after reinstalling the ZN414 integrated circuit), get an account at Kreditanstalt für Wiederaufbau (KfW), take an Erythromycin tablet, activate your radar, load your M16, peer over the Inner German Border, order Ordine Nuovo to crush the GRU and KGB spy rings in NATO, phone the White House, prime the ACLMs and fire your Davy Crockett Weapon System at the Symbionese Liberation Army's symbolic Collective farm before they steal our Fouga CM.170 Magisters and loot the our RAF base! There is a Cold War data base, interesting images, maps and videos, and map games. Map games are a popular phenomenon on many sites, including (in time) some planned games this one.
